@page "/cookies"
@layout MarketingLayout

<PageTitle>Cookie Policy - NavTour</PageTitle>
<HeadContent>
    <meta name="description" content="NavTour cookie policy describing the cookies and similar technologies used across the website and application." />
</HeadContent>

<section class="mkt-section">
    <div class="mkt-container mkt-legal-shell">
        <div class="reveal">
            <p class="mkt-eyebrow">Cookies</p>
            <h1>Cookie Policy</h1>
            <p class="mkt-legal-meta">Effective date: March 24, 2026</p>
        </div>

        <div class="mkt-legal-prose reveal" style="margin-top:var(--space-12)">
            <section>
                <h2>1. What this policy covers</h2>
                <p>
                    This Cookie Policy explains how NavTour uses cookies and similar technologies on the public website,
                    authenticated application, and related product surfaces.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2>2. Types of cookies we may use</h2>
                <ul class="mkt-legal-list">
                    <li>Essential cookies used for sign-in, session continuity, security, and core application behavior.</li>
                    <li>Preference cookies used to remember language, interface, or product settings where applicable.</li>
                    <li>Operational measurement cookies or similar storage used to understand product reliability and service performance.</li>
                </ul>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2>3. What we do not use by default</h2>
                <p>
                    NavTour does not present itself as an ad-tech or cross-site tracking platform. If additional analytics,
                    advertising, or third-party marketing technologies are introduced later, this policy should be updated
                    before they are used in production.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2>4. Browser controls</h2>
                <p>
                    Most browsers allow you to block or delete cookies. Disabling essential cookies may prevent sign-in
                    or other key product features from working correctly.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2>5. Related technologies</h2>
                <p>
                    NavTour may use local storage, session storage, or similar browser mechanisms where needed to support
                    authenticated sessions, product behavior, and user preferences. These technologies are treated in a
                    similar way to cookies for policy purposes.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2>6. Updates and contact</h2>
                <p>
                    We may update this policy as the product evolves. Questions about this policy or privacy practices can
                    be sent to <a href="mailto:support@navtour.cloud">support@navtour.cloud</a> or by mail to Avenida de
                    los Periodistas, PH Leaf Tower, Panama City, Panama.
                </p>
            </section>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>
